content:
**alon_upper_bound:**

∃ c₂ > 0 such that f(m) ≤ m/2 + c₂·m^{4/5}

This comes from constructing triangle-free graphs where the maximum bipartite subgraph is bounded.

**alon_lower_bound:**

∃ c₁ > 0 such that f(m) ≥ m/2 + c₁·m^{4/5}

Triangle-free graphs MUST have bipartite subgraphs significantly larger than m/2.

**erdos_581:**

Combines both bounds:
1. Lower: f(m) ≥ m/2 + c₁·m^{4/5}
2. Upper: f(m) ≤ m/2 + c₂·m^{4/5}

Status: SOLVED by Alon (1996)
